ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: The number of milliseconds since the start of the experiment until the questionnaire was completed
Ebbinghaus Illusion - What kind of block?
Ebbinghaus Illusion - Diameter of left circle
Ebbinghaus Illusion - Diameter of right circle
Ebbinghaus Illusion - Diameter of peripheral circles on left of screen
Ebbinghaus Illusion - Diameter of peripheral circles on right of screen
Ebbinghaus Illusion - Which ascii key they should press?
Ebbinghaus Illusion - Is the current trial a practice trial or not?

Notes: 0 = Participant did not identify the larger center circle; 1 = Participant correctly identified the larger center circle
